Name: falkonry-time-series-ai-suite
Abstract: The time series AI suite ingests operational data and provides insights and explanations on the surfacing anomalies that need human attention.
Description:
The automated classification system helps understand the various operating modes of the plant and help prioritize the plant operations, enabling greater uptime, throughput and quality. The solution scales across the plants with preferred deployment options - on-premise, edge or cloud. The time series AI suite includes the following features:

  • OT Data Pipeline: Securely transmit terabytes of time series data continuously or periodically to Falkonry so that the data can be visualized, explored, and organized on-demand. 
  • Time Series Database: Get fast access to data anytime from the high throughput, space-efficient and durable storage
  • Signal Management: Efficiently organize and group the input signals and AI-outputs into tree-like hierarchies. The grouping could be done on any parameter - geography, equipment type, sensor-type, etc - for visualizing and investigating signal properties over specific period of time
  • Anomaly detection: Assess the anomalies in signal data detected by AI through systematic identification of significant deviations from known normal operating behaviors 
  • Decision support: Make tacit knowledge executable by integrating digital decision-making into existing plant workflows
  • Case Reports: Compile a case report with analysis on select time ranges of signals, and collaborate with other users for conducting root cause analysis and documenting actionables.

Name: augury-machine-health
Abstract: Machine Health uses the Internet of Things (IOT) and Artificial Intelligence (AI) technology to predict and prevent industrial machine failures, and improve machine performance.
Description:
What is Machine Health? 

Machine Health uses the Internet of Things (IOT) and Artificial Intelligence (AI) technology to predict and prevent industrial machine failures, and improve machine performance.

How Does Machine Health Work? 

Augury’s full-stack Machine Health solutions use sensors that capture vibration, temperature and magnetic data from machines, advanced AI diagnostics and human reliability experts to improve the health and performance of industrial machines. Implement Machine Health in four easy steps (See our What is Machine Health video)     

  • Monitor: Sensors capture and transmit data to the Augury platform 24/7.     
  • Diagnose: AI detects issues, explains what caused them and prescribes courses of action.     
  • Guide: Augury’s platform, AI Insights and expert support enable users to prioritize and plan machine health activity.     
  • Act: Users collaborate and act on guidance to improve the health and performance of machines and operations.

 Machine Health CR: For Critical Equipment Expert-verified AI Diagnostics     

  • Specific Fault      
  • Fault Severity      
  • Fault Root Cause      
  • Recommended Maintenance Actions  

 Guaranteed Diagnostics  

  • Insurance-backed warranty for selected equipment 

Machine Health SE: For Supporting Equipment

Fully Autonomous AI Diagnostics   

  • Multiple possible fault diagnoses with associated confidence scores   
  • Your maintenance team confirms the correct diagnosis    
  • Digitize 60% more assets with cost-effective coverage

Name: corewatts
Abstract: CoreWatts collects and combines energy and production data from a plant to reveal trends in energy usage, machinery inefficiencies, and opportunities for saving money and creating sustainable practices. It represents this data through a visually rich and easy-to-use dashboard.
Description:
Much is at stake with the high investments associated with industries like manufacturing. Consequently, deciding on cost-effective and sustainable implementations cannot be left to assumptions or guesses- it must be backed by data. CoreWatts collects and combines energy and production data from a plant to reveal trends in energy usage, machinery inefficiencies, and opportunities for saving money and creating sustainable practices. It represents this data through a visually rich and easy-to-use dashboard. 

With CoreWatts, you will be able to: 

1. TRACK: Monitor the health of your plant, process, and equipment, tracking energy consumption and production data. 

2. SOLVE: Generate solutions from insights for energy-saving and productivity enhancements through machine learning. 

3. INTERVENTION: Plan based on your unique trends and make the necessary interventions to processes before the foreseen issue occurs. 

1. DIGITIZATION 4.0: Bolster the digitization of plant operations. 

2. ASSET MANAGEMENT: Detect when machines are losing efficiency and make calculated determinations on the long-term value of replacement versus repair. 

3. MATERIAL MANAGEMENT – Determine which raw materials give the best productivity efficiencies during processing. 

4. COMPLIANCE: Incorporate the guiding principles of the global leading energy management standard (ISO 50001)

Name: adapdix-edgeops
Abstract: Adapdix EdgeOps is an edge software platform that combines autonomous control with distributed DataMesh technology to enable autonomous manufacturing.
Description:
Solution Overview

Adapdix EdgeOps is an edge software platform that combines autonomous control with distributed DataMesh technology to enable autonomous manufacturing. EdgeOps’ containerized architecture captures, stores, analyzes, and synchronizes data, delivering machine intelligence and autonomous control of advanced manufacturing processes. It reduces latency and improves security, privacy, and cost, by bringing applications to your data rather than moving your data to the application.


Highlighted Benefits   

  • Improved Operational Efficiency: including reductions in unplanned downtime and increased production yield across advanced manufacturing environments. EdgeOps is easy to use and quick to deploy solution, with proven ROI in weeks.    
  • Reduced Data Management Costs: the Adapdix DataMesh is the first product in the market which encapsulate contemporary enterprise data management theory. It helps remove obstacles such as latency, security, privacy, and cloud cost, by facilitating a domain-based architecture. Adapdix DataMesh empowers end-users to link events across multiple data sources, bridging data silos.  This delivers higher application performance, better data quality, contextualization, and is a critical prerequisite for autonomous systems.    
  • Reduced TCO: Great to quantify opportunity through initial capex avoidance because improved productivity of current assets means you avoid buying additional new equipment.  



Value Differentiators  

  • Precision Control – Targets and improves performance of slowest performing and repetitive tasks   
  • Autonomous Operations – Self-correcting and self-optimizing capability converts high-touch task into autonomous functions with little or no human interaction   
  • Autonomous Learning – Seamlessly integrates process and control data in milliseconds increase precise, reactive, software-based task-level controls and improve decision-making   
  • Federated Learning – Greatly improves decision-making by scaling domain-based up to billions of rows or more at the edge to dramatically increase response and quality of data    
  • Non-disruptive - Runs alongside existing controls, no reprogramming and shutdowns.

Name: apogean
Abstract: Apogean™ lets you quickly connect legacy CNC equipment to collect data for smart manufacturing apps like OEE, manufacturing analytics, and any other manufacturing app or business system.
Description:
Apogean™ is the world’s only intelligent data collection solution that “speaks the same language” as all your smart manufacturing applications.  Use it to quickly connect legacy CNC equipment to capture data for smart manufacturing and improvement initiatives.  Apogean™ from Toward Zero is the only intelligent data collection solution that speaks OPC UA, MTConnect, MQTT, and automatically creates a machine profile for the CESMII SMIP.


Learn more about Apogean™ 

Request more info about Apogean™ 

Read about smart manufacturing  

  • Plug-and-play solution lets your manufacturing IT execute machine connectivity like an expert      
  • Lets you focus on smart manufacturing and continuous improvement instead of worrying about collecting machine data      
  • Easy monthly, quarterly, or annual subscription means you don’t have to buy or maintain expensive hardware


Now it's easy to collect data from CNC machines for OEE, shop floor analytics, and other apps.

Machine shops struggle to collect data from CNC machines for OEE, shop floor analytics, and other apps. Apogean™ by Toward Zero makes it quick and easy to collect data from CNC machines, without expensive PLC’s, complex wiring, or third-party conversion software. Apogean™ is a plug-and-play smart manufacturing data collection solution with onboard software to convert data from your CNC machine to almost any protocol needed for OEE, manufacturing analytics, MES, or other smart manufacturing application.

No more expensive hardware, software, infrastructure, or additional network drops. Apogean™ lets you use the same serial port or ethernet port for both CNC program and machine data collection.

Until recently, machine shops with legacy CNC machines that wanted to collect data for OEE, MES, analytics, or smart manufacturing apps had limited options:      

  1. Use widely available apps and exclude legacy CNC equipment from the initiative      
  2. Give up and do nothing


Flexibility with Apogean™



With Apogean™, data flows both directions using the serial port or ethernet port on your CNC equipment. Apogean™ “speaks the same language” as your equipment and converts the machine data into other protocols so you can use any analytics or smart manufacturing program in the CESMII marketplace or in the global market. It also means that you don’t have to change your data collection method or architecture if you change your mind later about applications, or want to try new ones as they come on the market.


As a result, you can capture and leverage data from every critical CNC machine. What does that mean for your machine shop with legacy equipment? Machine tools generate hundreds of data points every millisecond, but not every smart manufacturing software application “speaks” the same language as your smart manufacturing app. If you want to use industrial analytics and apps, you need a quick, inexpensive way to get your legacy machine data over to common systems like:      

  • OEE / shop floor analytics      
  • MES      
  • Tool life monitoring      
  • Predictive maintenance      
  • Energy monitoring      
  • Quality      
  • Plant scheduling systems      
  • Asset performance management


There’s no reason to mothball your legacy CNC machine or exclude it from your analytics initiative because you can’t collect data from it. Free your legacy machine data with the world’s only intelligent data collection solution that “speaks the same language” as all the smart manufacturing applications on the market today.
